Justification:  
C11 requires that for every minimal semantic basis of the claim, there exists at least one P-type argument whose justification contains that basis. The claim is "Shiloh is selfless." The minimal semantic bases for this claim would include propositions like "Shiloh acts for the benefit of others" or "Shiloh is not primarily motivated by self-interest."  

The P-type arguments provided focus on Shiloh lacking good intentions and gaining knowledge, which do not semantically cover all possible minimal bases for selflessness. Specifically, the P arguments do not contain justifications that subsume the semantic content of supporting arguments like "Shiloh inspires others" or "Shiloh could enhance the lives of others," which are directly relevant to selflessness. Since the P arguments' justifications are not semantic supersets of all minimal support bases for the claim, C11 is not satisfied.